com.dataloom.linking

Interface LinkingApi


  • public interface LinkingApi
    This API is used for creating and managing synthetic entity sets created by linking several entity sets together. The entity sets created by this invoking this API are not actually instantiated until they are accessed via the DataApi, which dynamically weaves them together based on the matching information.

      • createLinkingEntityType

        @POST(value="/datastore/linking/type")
java.util.UUID createLinkingEntityType(LinkingEntityType linkingEntityType)
        Creates an entity type describing the result of linking several entity types together. This entity type will be be usable in entity set searches.
        Parameters:
        linkingEntityType - The linking entity type
        Returns:
        The UUID of the linked entity type.

      • linkEntitySets

        @POST(value="/datastore/linking/set")
java.util.UUID linkEntitySets(@Body
                                                                    LinkingEntitySet linkingEntitySet)
        Performs linking operation on entity sets. The entity type of the set must have already been defined by a call to createLinkingEntityType(LinkingEntityType).
        Parameters:
        linkingEntitySet - An entity set definition consisting of an entity set and associated properties to link on. Each map in linking propertiesmust be the same length, with entity set ids as a keys and property type ids as values. If no maps are provided, an empty linking entity set is created that can be populated by calling linkEntities(UUID, UUID, UUID, Set).
        Returns:
        The id of the new entity set constructed from linking the desired entity sets.
